ko.alarm_ftp_info: FTP 서버를 활성화해야 파일 업로드를 통해 움직임을 트리거할 수 있습니다!
ko.alarm_http_info: HTTP 서버를 활성화해야 HTTP 호출을 통해 움직임을 트리거할 수 있습니다!
ko.alarm_http_reset_info: HTTP 서버를 활성화해야 HTTP 호출을 통해 움직임을 초기화할 수 있습니다!
ko.alarm_smtp_info: SMTP 서버를 활성화해야 이메일을 통해 움직임을 트리거할 수 있습니다!
ko.analyze_duration_info: 입력을 확인하기 위해 필요한 시간을 microsecond로 지정하세요. 높은 값을 사용하면 더 정확하게 탐지하지만, 레이턴시를 증가시킵니다. 기본값은 5,000,000 microseconds = 5초 (-analyzeduration) 입니다.
ko.audio_codec_info: HSV 용으로 HomeKit에 보내는 음성을 인코딩할 코덱을 설정하세요. 반드시 AAC 기반이어야 합니다 (-acodec).
ko.audio_codec_info_hksv: HKSV 용으로 HomeKit에 보내는 음성을 인코딩할 코덱을 설정하세요. 반드시 AAC 기반이어야 합니다 (-acodec).
ko.backup_info_download: 전체 camera.ui 환경의 백업 아카이브를 다운로드합니다. 이 기능은 당신의 camera.ui 저장 디렉터리에서 녹화를 포함한 모든 내용을 백업합니다. 나중에 camera.ui를 사용하는 다른 플랫폼에서 이것을 복원할 수 있습니다.
ko.backup_info_restore: camera.ui를 사용해 만들었던 백업 아카이브를 복원합니다. 당신의 camera.ui 설정, 데이터베이스, 녹화 그리고 camera.ui 계정이 복원됩니다.
ko.backup_info_shedule: camera.ui 데이터베이스의 전체 백업은 매일 12:00:00에 생성되며, 7일간 보관됩니다.
ko.bitrate_info_hksv: HKSV에 사용되는 최대 비트레이트(kbit/s)입니다. 지정하지 않으면 HomeKit이 요청하는 비트레이트를 사용합니다 (-b:v).
ko.camera_settings_save_info: Fields marked with (¹) can be saved only by clicking the "✓" button
ko.cameras_nav_info: Manage the streaming parameters of the cameras
ko.debug_info: Includes debugging output from the main FFmpeg process in the log.
ko.disable_info: Disables the camera and removes it from HomeKit.
ko.doorbellSensor_info: Exposes the doorbell device for this camera. This can be triggered with the dummy switches, MQTT messages, or via HTTP, depending on what features are enabled in the config.
ko.dwell_time_info: Dwell time means that after a Motion Detector is tripped it will need a N-seconds period in which it detects no motion in order to "reset" back to its default detection mode. This prevents the sensor from sending out multiple alerts for the same motion
ko.email_body_lookup_info: If camera.ui can't find out the name of the camera by the email address, you can enter a term here so that camera.ui can search the text content of the email for this term and thus assign the camera
ko.email_from_info: The email from address (without everything after @) to be assigned to this camera (e.g. my test camera. If not defined, the camera name will be used)
ko.email_to_info: The email to address (without everything after @) to be assigned to this camera (e.g. my test camera. If not defined, the camera name will be used)
ko.encoder_options_info: Options to be passed to the video encoder.
ko.encoder_options_info_hksv: Options to be passed to the video encoder for the HKSV recording process.
ko.excludeSwitch_info: Exposes a 'exclude' switch to HomeKit to exclude/include the camera from the interface settings within HomeKit.
ko.forceClose_timer_info: Timer in minutes that automatically interrupts (resets) the constant detection of motion after N minutes. 0 = Disabled. Attention: If the timer is deactivated, it is up to the camera WHEN the motion detection is considered "finished" and thus the recording is stopped. This can lead to very long recordings!
ko.forgotpw_content: If you have forgotten your password, you can restore it by deleting the database or importing a backup.
ko.fps_info: The fps used for video stream.
ko.fps_info_hksv: The maximum frame rate used for HKSV. If not set, will use any size HomeKit requests (-r).
ko.height_info: The height used for video stream.
ko.height_info_hksv: The maximum height used for HKSV. If not set, will use any size HomeKit requests (-s).
ko.help_started: To help you get started and provide good experience with camera.ui, please complete the following configuration.
ko.homebridge_restart_info: Changing the fields marked with (²) requires restart of Homebridge
ko.interface_nav_info: Create new rooms or make other settings
ko.label: Label
ko.livestream_snapshot: Switches between live stream or snapshot interval
ko.loglevel_info: Show only defined log level (Info = Show informative messages during processing. This is in addition to warnings and errors - Debug: Show everything, including debugging information - Warning: Show only warnings and errors - Error: Show only errors)
ko.manufacturer_info: Set the manufacturer name for display in the Home app
ko.map_audio_info: Selects the stream used for audio (-map).
ko.map_video_info: Selects the stream used for video (-map).
ko.max_delay_info: When receiving data over UDP, the demuxer tries to reorder received packets (since they may arrive out of order, or packets may get lost totally). This can be disabled by setting the maximum demuxing delay to zero (-max_delay).
ko.max_streams_info: The maximum number of streams that will be allowed at once to this camera.
ko.model_info: Set the model for display in the Home app
ko.motionDoorbellSwitch_info: Enables dummy switches to trigger motion and/or doorbell, if either of those are enabled. When enabled there will be an additional switch that triggers the motion or doorbell event.
ko.motionDoorbell_info: Rings the doorbell when motion is activated. This allows for motion alerts to appear on Apple TVs.
ko.motionSensor_info: Exposes the motion sensor for this camera. This can be triggered with the dummy switches, MQTT messages, or via HTTP, depending on what features are enabled in the config.
ko.motion_timeout_info: The number of seconds after triggering to reset the motion sensor. Set to 0 to disable resetting of motion trigger.
ko.name: Name
ko.notfound_message: Sorry, the page you're looking for doesn't exist.
ko.notification_text: @ detected a new movement in room %
ko.notifications_alert: You have a total of % notifications
ko.notifications_nav_info: Manage the Alexa, Telegram and Webhook settings
ko.page_not_found: The page you requested could not be found.
ko.pixel_difference_info: The color difference required to trigger motion on a pixel (the smaller the value the smaller the color difference and the larger the value the larger the color difference needed to register it as movement)
ko.press_enter_to_create: Press %Enter% to create a new label
ko.privacyMode_info: Turn off the camera feed and replace it with a privacy image in HomeKit
ko.privacySwitch_info: Exposes a 'privacyMode' switch to replace the camera feed with a privacy image in HomeKit
ko.probe_size_info: Set probing size in bytes, i.e. the size of the data to analyze to get stream information. A higher value will enable detecting more information in case it is dispersed into the stream, but will increase latency. Must be an integer not lesser than 32. It is 5000000 by default (-probesize).
ko.read_rate_info: Read input at native frame rate (-re).
ko.record_on_movement_info: Enables recording video (eg on movement) through UI and NOT through external controller.
ko.recording_text: The @ was taken on % by a #.
ko.recording_timer_not_editable: Recording time cannot be edited. Settings can be changed in config.json.
ko.recording_type_not_editable: Recording type cannot be edited. Settings can be changed in config.json.
ko.recordings_alert: You have % recordings in total and # recordings were selected
ko.recordings_nav_info: Manage the recording settings and specify the recording type
ko.rekognition_nav_info: Image analysis for motion detection via Amazon Rekognition
ko.remove_all_confirm_text: After clicking 'Remove all' all stored @ will be irrevocably deleted. Are you sure?
ko.remove_camera_confirm_text: Do you really want to delete the camera '@'?
ko.remove_camera_confirm_text_homebridge: Do you really want to delete the camera '@'? This will also remove the camera from Homebridge!
ko.reorder_queue_size_info: Packets may be received out of order, so before they can be passed onwards, they need to be reordered. Default jitter buffer size is 500. This option allows you to specify it manually. Higher values will lead to greater latency. Only applicable for reception over UDP (-reorder_queue_size).
ko.reset_confirm_text: After clicking 'Reset' all stored data will be irrevocably deleted. Are you sure?
ko.restart_confirm_text: Do you really want to reboot @?
ko.rss_feed_widget_info: Please enter a valid RSS URL to see the feed in the widget.
ko.sensitivity_info: The percentage of pixels (see Differnce) required to trigger a movement (a low sensitivity means that more pixel differences have to be detected, a high sensitivity means that less pixel differences have to be detected)
ko.serialNumber_info: Set the serial number for display in the Home app
ko.shortcuts_widget_info: Please select the action from the list to show it in the shortcuts.
ko.source_info: FFmpeg options on where to find and how to decode your camera's video stream. The most basic form is '-i' followed by your camera's URL.
ko.source_info_hksv: Here you can set a custom video source for HKSV recordings only.
ko.start_end_message:
And thats it.
Have fun with camera.ui!
ko.start_info_message:
You must change your credentials
before logging in to camera.ui
ko.still_image_source_info: If your camera also provides a URL for a still image, that can be defined here with the same syntax as 'source'. If not set, camera.ui will grab one frame from 'source'.
ko.sub_source_info: Low Resolution Substream. FFmpeg options on where to find and how to decode your camera's video substream. The most basic form is '-i' followed by your camera's URL. The substream will be used to probe the stream or for motion detection through video analysis.
ko.system_nav_info: Manage the backend settings of camera.ui
ko.telegram_type_not_editable: Telegram cannot be changed for this camera.
ko.timeout_info: Socket TCP I/O timeout in seconds. If you have problems with hanging FFmpeg processes in the background, you can enter any value here to stop the process automatically after the entered time, if no response comes (-stimeout).
ko.unbridge_info: 브릿지된 카메라는 전체 Homebridge 인스턴스를 느리게 할 수 있습니다. 대신 브릿지되지 않은 카메라는 Homekit에 직접 추가해야 합니다.
ko.video_codec_info: Set the codec used for encoding video sent to HomeKit, must be H.264-based. You can change to a hardware accelerated video codec with this option, if one is available (-vcodec).
ko.video_codec_info_hksv: Set the codec used for encoding video for HKSV, must be H.264-based. You can change to a hardware accelerated video codec with this option, if one is available (-vcodec).
ko.video_filter_info: Comma-delimited list of additional video filters for FFmpeg to run on the video. If 'none' is included, the default video filters are disabled (-filter:v).
ko.videoanalysis_info: 움직임 감지를 위한 비디오 분석을 활성화합니다 (저해상도 하위 스트림 사용을 추천합니다. 그렇지 않으면 prebuffering이 활성화됩니다.)
ko.weather_widget_info: 날씨 위젯을 활성화하려면 도시 이름을 영어로 검색해주세요.
ko.welcome_submessage: 당신의 RTSP 카메라를 위한 웹 인터페이스
ko.width_info_hksv: HKSV에 사용될 최대 너비입니다. 입력하지 않으면 HomeKit이 요청하는 사이즈를 사용합니다 (-s).
